Chicken Cross Road Work Plan (10 Weeks)

Week 1: Project Initializing & Player Input System
Objective:
Set up Java development environment and create the basic game structure.
Activities:
- Install and configure Java JDK.
- Configure VS Code for Java development.
- Create project folder structure.
- Create main game window using Java Swing.
- Implement game loop.
- Add keyboard input controls.
Deliverables:
- Main.java
- Basic game window
- Keyboard movement system
Expected Outcome:
Player can move using keyboard controls.




Week 2: Grid-Based Movement & Camera System
Objective:
Implement Cross Road style movement.
Activities:
- Create grid-based movement system.
- Restrict player movement to tiles.
- Add smooth movement animation.
- Create camera scrolling system.
- Manage game coordinates.
Deliverables:
- Updated Player.java
- Camera.java
- Movement system
Expected Outcome:
Player moves smoothly through the game world.

Week 3: Environment Development
Objective:
Create the game environment.
Activities:
- Design grass area.
- Create road area.
- Create river area.
- Implement tile-based map system.
- Add background objects.
Deliverables:
- Map.java
- Tile.java
- Environment system

Expected Outcome:
Player can move through different environments.

Week 4: Vehicle System Implementation
Objective:
Add moving obstacles.
Activities:
- Create Vehicle class.
- Implement car movement.
- Add vehicle spawning system.
- Create multiple vehicle types.
- Control vehicle speed.
Deliverables:
- Vehicle.java
- VehicleSpawner.java
Expected Outcome:
Cars move continuously across the road.

Week 5: Collision Detection & Player Death System
Objective:
Implement collision mechanics.
Activities:
- Add collision detection.
- Detect player and vehicle collision.
- Create player death system.
- Add restart functionality.
- Create GameManager class.
Deliverables:
- Collision.java
- GameManager.java
Expected Outcome:
Player dies when hit by vehicles and game over appears.

Week 6: River & Floating Object Mechanics
Objective:
Add advanced environment hazards.
Activities:
- Create floating logs.
- Add river movement.
- Implement water collision.
- Allow player movement with logs.
Deliverables:
- Log.java
- RiverSystem.java
Expected Outcome:
Player can cross rivers using floating objects.

Week 7: Score System & Procedural Map Generation
Objective:
Create endless gameplay.
Activities:
- Add score calculation.
- Track player progress.
- Generate random road/river sections.
- Create increasing difficulty.
Deliverables:
- Score.java
- LevelGenerator.java
Expected Outcome:
Game world generates dynamically with scoring.
Week 8: Optimization & Audio Integration
Objective:
Improve performance and game experience.
Activities:
- Optimize object creation.
- Remove unused objects.
- Add sound effects.
- Add background music.
Deliverables:
- AudioManager.java
- Optimized game engine
Expected Outcome:
Smooth gameplay with sound support.

Week 9: User Interface & Date Persistence
Objective:
Create complete game interface.
Activities:
- Create main menu.
- Add score display.
- Create game over screen.
- Add restart and exit buttons.
- Save high score using files.
Deliverables:
- UIManager.java
- SaveSystem.java
Expected Outcome:
Game has complete UI and saved high scores.


Week 10: Testing & Final Deployment
Objective:
Prepare final project.
Activities:
- Test all features.
- Fix bugs.
- Improve code structure.
- Apply OOP principles.
- Create executable package.
- Prepare documentation.
Deliverables:
- Final Java project
- Source code
- Documentation
- Demo video
Expected Outcome:
A complete playable 2D Chicken Cross Road game.
